column14: Estimated flow. </=0.001cms 13:35: Found float just above level of intake, pin is approx 3cm from hitting bottom of cabinet. Switch shaft float and weight so the float is away from intake. The float interferes with the ETG weight now and will have to be move aside at each ETG reading but it is better than hitting the intake. 13:49 SDI command aS0+0.467! to set shaft reading to 0.467m. Shaft screen changed accordingly. Next SDI command aS1-0.375! to change the direction of the wheel because float switched sides. Moved float by hand and confirmed direction is correct. Pinned float at next interval - intake will go out of water before pin is caught.  Mid-section
